-- Levitt Says SEC Figuring Out High Frequency Trading (Audio)
-- B y
-- 2012-10-08T14:30:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-08/levitt-says-sec-figuring-out-high-frequency-trading-audio-.html
Arthur Levitt , former U.S. Securities
and Exchange Commission Chairman, says it is "a good idea" for 
the SEC to go directly to the high frequency trading industry to
formulate sensible regulation. Levitt talks with Bloomberg's Tom
Keene on Bloomberg Radio's "Bloomberg Surveillance." The are 
joined by Joshua Shapiro of MFR.   (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 05:29
 